# Orchestration Rules (Vibe-Coder v3.0)

## When to Use Multi-Agent Coordination

Use the mega-orchestrator when a task involves:
- 3+ files changing simultaneously
- Both frontend and backend changes
- Both implementation and testing
- Architecture decisions + implementation
- Full feature development

## OMC Team Pipeline
```
team-plan → team-prd → team-exec → team-verify → team-fix (loop)
```

Use: `COMBINED/orchestration/core-omc/`

## Superpowers Workflow (Universal)
```
1. brainstorming → refine ideas
2. git-worktrees → isolated workspace
3. writing-plans → bite-sized tasks (2-5 min each)
4. test-driven-development → RED-GREEN-REFACTOR
5. code-review → review against plan
6. finishing-branch → verify tests, present options
```

Use: `COMBINED/orchestration/superpowers/`

## GSD Spec-Driven Development
```
gsd:spec → extract specification
gsd:plan → generate implementation plan
gsd:exec → execute the plan
```

Use: `COMBINED/orchestration/core-gsd/`

## MCP Tools for Orchestration
```
mcp gitnexus map               — understand codebase
mcp code-review-graph build     — structural analysis
mcp supermemory search <query>  — check prior work
```

## Agent Files
Full orchestrator: `COMBINED/agents/mega/mega-orchestrator.md`
